=== DISTRESS_SIGNAL ===
# id: 94
# title: The Distress Signal Terminal
# chinese_title: 求救信号
# category: Terminal
# mode: dungeon

A communications terminal is broadcasting a repeating distress signal on an old frequency. The message is garbled but mentions survivors, coordinates, and a plea for supplies. The signal originated from somewhere nearby — perhaps within this very station.

* [Trace the signal to its source]
  ~ gain_radical("口")
  "呼" (hū) — to call, to cry out. The radical "口" (kǒu) means mouth.
* [Boost the signal so rescue ships can hear it]
  ~ gain_xp(20)
  "发" (fā) — to send, to emit
* [Respond to the signal]
  ~ gain_xp(15)
  "答" (dá) — to answer, to respond
* [Ignore it — it could be a trap]
  ~ nothing
  "假" (jiǎ) — false, fake
